 "summary_en": "Archive documents trace planning for Pier 70. A 1986 Mission Bay study weighs a \"consolidated Pier 70 and 80\" container terminal against separate terminals at Piers 50, 70 and 80. Port Commission minutes from 2004 describe Pier 70 as \"home of the ship repair industry.\" A 2011 agenda notes the Department of Defense \"awarded the Port a total of $2.28 million\" for environmental clean-up. A 2015 agenda presents a Forest City mixed-use plan, a proposed Pier 70 Special Use District, and a BAE Systems lease of \"approximately 14.4 acres improved with 19 buildings.\" Pier 70 is operated by the Port of San Francisco, whose FY2025 budget line is $156M; capital records show $7,827,325.29 paid to Historic Pier 70 LLC.",
 "published": true,
